    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-12-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-12-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="104" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Harvey</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 162.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-12-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 27, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 3d of December, No.
                            305, has been received. The proceedings which you took on the occasion
                            of the birth-day of the Emperor of Brazil were proper and
                            commendable.</p>
                <p>This government does not feel serious embarrassment in regard to the
                            affair at Bahia. It reposes confidence enough in the public strength and
                            virtue to insist on its own rights, and to recognize the just rights of
                            other nations.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James E. Harvey,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c. Lisbon.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
